## Statistical Analysis
A weighted analysis of variance (ANOVA), followed by Student’s t-test (p < 0.05), was used for assessing physicochemical differences among the experiments, according to Mira-García et al. (2024). Further, the data were analyzed using a two-way ANOVA with irrigation water qualities and the two different growing environments as the main factors. The statistical analyses were performed with SPSS statistical software (v. 25.0, IBM Corporation Armonk, NY, USA).

